[...]
there  are two  alternators in use with an overlap of time periods and=20=

if the alternator was replaced it will be with the later one.  the=20
differences were primarily in the shape of the voltage regulator=20
module.  www.bus-boys.com has pictures of the two in the vanagon=20
charging system parts area.   make sure that the contact area for the=20
brushes  is smooth and shiny and not gouged or deeply worn  or  you =20
will  not get good mileage out of the replacement. the notes below=20
match  what i pulled out of  the etka  listing.
jimt
westydriver

070-903-803A=A0 Bosch Internal Voltage Regulator, Rectangular Housing=20
with Brushes (30062), 1980 to 1981

068-903-803B=A0 Bosch Internal Voltage Regulator, Round Button Housing=20=

with Brushes (30091), 1980 to 1983

